# Frontend Rules

## General

This is a **desktop-first React web application**. Do not produce mobile-app-style page structures unless explicitly requested.

Preferred frontend patterns:
- sidebar navigation
- top header / toolbar
- content area with cards, forms, tables, summaries
- multi-step workflows
- dashboard panels
- empty / loading / error states

Avoid:
- bottom tab bars
- full-screen mobile card stacks as the default web layout
- narrow phone-width centered pages unless intentional
- mobile-first interaction assumptions for core desktop pages

## Visual Direction

The reference Figma provides the visual language, not the final interaction model.

Use:
- soft neutral/pale background
- white or near-white cards
- subtle shadows
- large but controlled border radii
- generous spacing
- clear content hierarchy
- restrained accent colors

Do not:
- recreate a fake phone frame in the UI
- mirror mobile navigation structures
- overuse floating decorative elements
- make the app look like a finance-dribbble clone without practical usability

## Component Preferences

Prefer reusable components for: app shell, sidebar, header, stats cards, filing status cards, summary panels, form sections, data tables, upload panels, empty states, validation summaries.

Always split complex screens into components. Do not leave large pages as one giant JSX file.

## Frontend State

Prefer:
- local component state for isolated UI state
- form libraries for form state
- server-state tools for async remote data if already present in the project
- predictable typed APIs

Avoid:
- unnecessary global state
- duplicated derived state
- deeply nested prop drilling when composition or context is cleaner
- putting business rules directly in presentational components

## Data Fetching

Prefer server-safe and framework-consistent patterns. Do not invent ad hoc client fetching if the codebase already has a pattern.

Avoid:
- inconsistent fetching styles across pages
- embedding large fetch logic directly in UI components
- mixing unrelated data concerns in one component
